{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# error Library Demo 🧠\n",
    "\n",
    "Welcome to the demonstration of `error`. This notebook shows how the library translates confusing exceptions into plain-English solutions, captures scope variables safely, groups logs, and simplifies debugging."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Initialization and Configuration\n",
    "\n",
    "To start, import `error` and enable `humanize()`. We will also set the traceback mode to `full` to get detailed reports."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import error\n",
    "\n",
    "# Enable error formatting\n",
    "error.humanize(True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configure settings\n",
    "error.configure(traceback_mode=\"full\", mask_secrets=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Error Explanation and suggestions\n",
    "\n",
    "We can catch exceptions and use `error.explain(exc)` to render beautiful HTML solutions inside Jupyter Notebooks."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    my_dict = {\"name\": \"Alice\"}\n",
    "    val = my_dict[\"age\"]\n",
    "except KeyError as exc:\n",
    "    # Renders a premium HTML card in Jupyter!\n",
    "    display(error.explain(exc))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Local Variable Snapshots (`@capture_locals`)\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's see how `@capture_locals` captures local variables at the moment of an error, while automatically masking passwords and tokens."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@error.capture_locals\n",
    "def login_and_calculate(username, api_key, factor):\n",
    "    # trigger division by zero\n",
    "    result = 100 / factor\n",
    "    return result\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    login_and_calculate(\"admin_user\", \"super-secret-token-12345\", 0)\n",
    "except ZeroDivisionError as exc:\n",
    "    display(error.diagnose(exc))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4. Resilient Decorators (`@retry` and `@fallback`)\n",
    "\n",
    "Add retry and fallback handlers easily to your methods:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fallback returns a default value on error\n",
    "@error.fallback(default=0.0)\n",
    "def divide_safe(a, b):\n",
    "    return a / b\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Fallback division:\", divide_safe(10, 0))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Retry will attempt execution multiple times before failing\n",
    "calls = 0\n",
    "@error.retry(tries=3, delay=0.1, jitter=True, exceptions=(ValueError,))\n",
    "def fetch_data():\n",
    "    global calls\n",
    "    calls += 1\n",
    "    if calls < 3:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(\"Connection timeout\")\n",
    "    return \"Data loaded!\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Retry result:\", fetch_data())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5. Type and Value Comparison (`error.compare`)\n",
    "\n",
    "If you want to explain why a type or value mismatch occurred, use `error.compare`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare int expected against string got\n",
    "display(error.compare(expected=int, got=str, value=\"hello\"))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6. Error Analytics Grouping\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's see the recorded errors grouped together with counts and a visual bar graph representation!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Renders a styled HTML table with frequency charts\n",
    "display(error.get_analytics())"
   ]
  }
 ],
